        "summary": "## Goal\n1. Set up automated session maintenance (completed)\n2. Improve daily preparation/forward-looking info for Bobby\n3. Add Finnly's vet appointment to iCloud calendar (completed)\n4. Understand and potentially integrate GLM 5.1 as a free alternative/larger-context AI model\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Bobby prefers fully automated calendar events — \"you should just add it and tell me it's done, I shouldn't have to click anything\"\n- Calendar integration requires using exact name \"Family Calendar\" (not \"Family\")\n- Uses Telegram for all communication\n- Currently running OpenClaw with MiniMax M2.7 as primary model\n- Nightly Intel at 10:26 PM collects cash-on-hand + bills paid\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Session cleanup freed 544MB (1346 old cron session files deleted, sessions.json cleared from 85MB)\n- [x] Weekly Session Cleanup cron created — every Sunday 3 AM EDT, ID: `6c87956b-dd85-4e4e-8f7d-6c9384c9f9d7`, sends Telegram summary to Bobby after each run\n- [x] Finnly's bath & nail trim added to \"Family Calendar\" (exact name) — April 15, 8:15 AM, Petsmart Turkey Creek\n- [x] Explained GLM 5.1: Zhipu AI model, free cloud tier, 204,800 token context window, OpenAI-compatible API at `https://api.z.ai/api/paas/v4/`\n- [x] Tax Day bills paid Apr 15: Cap One $25 + Discover $25 + GEICO $187.25 = $237.25 (Bobby had $239)\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Bobby considering whether to set up GLM 5.1 as backup/larger-context model in OpenClaw\n- [ ] Bills in family calendar still pending (4+ days)\n- [ ] Content Manager skill ready for @profittopanic\n\n### Blocked\n- MC calendar API routes not found (ports 3001 and 8788 respond with `{\"error\":\"Not found\"}`)\n- AppleScript required correct calendar name \"Family Calendar\" — failed with \"Family\" before diagnosis\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Weekly cleanup cron**: Scheduled because sessions.json hit 85MB which is bloated and slows gateway\n- **Calendar AppleScript fix**: Used `python3 subprocess.run(['osascript', '-e', script])` to avoid heredoc quoting issues; used `\"Family Calendar\"` as the exact calendar name\n- **GLM 5.1**: Not currently configured in OpenClaw; would require ZAI API key signup + provider/model config\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Bobby to decide on GLM 5.1 setup — needs free API key from z.ai, then add ZAI provider to OpenClaw config\n2. Collect nightly intel cash numbers from Bobby (missed 10:26 PM slot)\n3. Update memory file with today's events (Tax Day, Finnly appt added)\n4. Address pending \"bills in family calendar\" task (4+ days)\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Finnly appointment**: Wed Apr 15 8:15 AM, Petsmart Turkey Creek, bath & nail trim\n- **OpenClaw config**: `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` — has minimax-portal and grok-xai providers; ZAI not yet configured\n- **Calendar correct name**: \"Family Calendar\" (space included) — not \"Family\"\n- **Ports**: Mission Control on port 8788; calendar API routes unknown\n- **MC data files**: `~/agent-mission-control/data/` has balances.json, bills.json, finnly.json, habits.json, money.json, shared-memory.json\n- **Money tracker CSVs**: `~/Desktop/money-tracker/bobby.csv` — contains Doordash income and Target Finnly Food expenses\n- **Session cleanup command**: `openclaw sessions cleanup --enforce --all-agents`\n- **GLM 5.1 cost**: $0 input, $0 output; context window 204,800 tokens; max output 131,072 tokens\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Original Request\nUser (B G / Bobby) asked if the assistant read the full article in an X post: https://x.com/shmidtqq/status/2044027418541691041\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant attempted web_fetch to read the article → failed (X blocked)\n- Attempted browser.open to navigate to the X post\n- Took a browser snapshot but the page content was truncated (13,557+ characters) before the assistant could process the article content\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe assistant was in the process of reading the X post via browser to extract the full article content. The snapshot captured raw X page DOM elements (navigation, buttons, etc.) but the actual article content was not yet parsed or summarized before the truncation occurred. The retained suffix likely contains the continuation of the assistant reading and processing the page content.\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-14.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-15.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.json\n</read-files>",
